Resolution:
MyItems can hide attachments BUT that stops the user from uploading and throws an error when opening a Catalogue item.

Role rights: making the attachments object add enabled but not view/edit enabled, also throws an error when opening the Catalogue item, where the Attachment block is present.


Solution 1:
Allocate all users with an SM login and allocate SelfService Role.
Make the Requested for field mandatory and populate values on parent SR, from the Service Catalogue Item (SCI) AND
Via SQL populate the current records with the concatenated First & Last Name field values.
Individual users can then log on and view their SR/INC themselves PLUS Store login can then be allocated to the Manager level only (change the password too),  to view all items logged for that Store, using MyItems functionality (as users are linked to a Store).
Add a confidentiality Boolean field, which would then make the logged tickets visible, via Full UI, to only the HR Team members and no other roles (except Self Service *see point above*).

Solution 2:
Allocate all users a SM login and allocated SelfService Role OR Keep the current process (Store Login’s).
Complete the Requested fields, so to allow for the linking to the Employee Profile (if not, then can use the current Store Profile).
Create a workflow, to move all attachments from the logged INC/SR to the Profile record (either Store or Requested for Profile or both, using roll-up functionality, it can still be made visible to HR Roles, in full User UI).
Attachments will then be linked directly to the Profile and SM Layouts can be updated to show the roll-up attachments.
Add a confidentiality Boolean field, which would then make the logged tickets visible, via Full UI, to only the HR Team members and no other roles.

Solution 3:
Keep current process (Store Login).
Complete the Requested fields, so to allow for the linking to the Employee Profile.
If not the above then, show it on the ticket’s Store Profile).
Create a workflow, to move all attachments from the logged INC/SR to the Profile record (either Store or Requested for Profile or both, using roll-up functionality, it can still be made visible to HR Roles, in full User UI).
Attachments will then be linked directly to the Profile and SM INC/SR/Task Layouts can be updated to show the roll-up attachments. This is easier to implement (1-1 relationship) vs 1 SR Multiple Tasks.
Add a confidentiality Boolean field, which would then make the logged tickets visible, via Full UI, to only the HR Team members and no other roles. Can be extended to Tasks too.

Solution 4:
Keep current process (Store Login).
Complete the Requested fields, so to allow for the direct linking of the created ticket to the Employee Profile. ( If need be, allocate all Dischem users SelfService, authentication via Internal password or external authentication method.)
If not creating individual logins, then, show on the ticket’s Store Profile *current process*
Create a workflow, to move all attachments from the logged INC/SR to the Profile record (either Store or Requested for Profile or both. By using the roll-up functionality, it can still be made visible to HR Roles, in full User UI.
Attachments will then be moved to be directly on the SM Profile. SM INC/SR/Task Layouts updated to show the roll-up attachments that are now on Profile.
Add a confidentiality Boolean field, which would then make the logged tickets visible, via Full UI, to only the HR Team members and no other roles. Can be extended to Tasks too.
